entities.description: The frequency of responses for specific survey items.
The raw count of responses for survey items without any statistical weighting.
The percentage representation of the unweighted frequency for survey items.
Data points that are missing or not provided in the survey responses.
Statistical measures (e.g., mean, median, mode, maximum, minimum) of survey responses.
Survey item measuring the count of premises (locations) entered by the respondent.
Total number of cases or responses collected in the survey.

relationships.description: Relates the response frequency to the unweighted count of responses.
Relates the response frequency to the percentage representation of the responses.
Indicates the presence of missing data in the survey responses.
Relates the survey to various statistical measures of the responses.
Relates the survey item about the number of premises entered to the frequency of responses.
Indicates that response frequency is part of the total case count.
